de_favela_rio_dusk,night&dawn mappack

Now you can play de_favela_rio "from dusk till dawn".

This is a mappack with 3 new lighting versions of de_favela_rio.

de_favela_rio_dusk --> dusk version
de_favela_rio_night --> night version
de_favela_rio_dawn --> dawn version

The lay-out is exactly the same as already released de_favela_rio with day lighting.

The map plays songs that are not included in the BSP, and must be installed manually.

Instructions for installation of songs:

The mappack includes the folder de_favela, with 6 mp3 music files, to be installed in the folder ...cstrike/sound. If you wish, you can change the music files to your liking, just name them music1, music2... music6. To toggle songs, press use key (default <E>) in front of the stereo.

Note on the radar bug: If the radar does not appear, check the parameter cl_radaralpha, it must be set between 0 and 255 but by default is 1, which is almost Transparent. Adjust to 100 or more.

Note on the effect of vegetation fade-out: The vegetation of the map fades out at a certain distance. To eliminate this effect, change the parameter cl_detaildist 1200 (default) to 3000.

This is a video on the map:

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Bl53hkx2GPM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

Have fun, and give me your feedback.

de_favela_day

This map is an improved version of de_favela. de_favela has some gameplay issues, first the map is too dark which makes difficult to see the enemy, second is too T sided. De_favela_day is supposed to fix these issues with a day-light lighting and some lay-out changes. Plus, it has some visual improvements.

I released this version as a new map, because I intend to keep de_favela with its sun-set / dusk lighting, and intend to release soon a version with further improvements on that map. Maybe even a night version.

All files included in the bsp, including nav.

Important note:

To play the map, after launching counter-strike source, its import NOT to run de_favela before, because many textures on both maps have the same name but were modified. So if you run de_favela the game will load the old textures and then changing to de_favela_day it will use these old textures previously loaded from de_favela. To fix this you have to exit the game and relaunch it, and run de_favela_day again. To avoid this inconvinient for good, I suggest to delete de_favela, or to move it from the maps directory. This rule goes also for other maps I released that were released before like cs_complexo2_v1 e cs_complexo2_v2 which also use textures with same name that were later modified for de_favela_day.

Thanks to Chizbone for the nav.

Thanks to all servers that played de_favela, allowing me to realize the gameplay issues and make the improvements, hope you approve this new map and keep it on your map rotation. Let me name some that I tracked:

-	|Front War|
-	HAVAIANA
-	GHOST
-	PCS Amigos das Antigas
-	TecHhpoint Lanhouse

So, its de_favela_day, tunned for top gameplay. Have fun. And I appreciate your feed-back.

de_favela_4dm (for Death Match)

This map is a de_favela version specially modified for Death Match mode, with a special feature: The CT and T spawn areas are surrounded by gates. The gates will cycle, open for 10 seconds and closed for 50 seconds, until the end of the round. The player will spawn instantly after death as usual in Death Match, but will have to wait until the next gate opening to rejoin the action. The idea is to slower a bit that “fast-and-furious” pace of DeathMatch mode, making it more tactical and team-play oriented. Players that are waiting for the next gate opening can plan the best strategy before rejoining the action.

Note: Death Match settings must be:

cssdm_spawn_method "none" (normal spawn points, not random)
cssdm_allow_c4 "1" (allow C4 in game)
Recommended settings for round:

round time: 10 minutes
C4 explosion time (mp_c4timer): 90 seconds
freeze time at round start: 3 seconds or less

I appreciate your feedback on this idea and on this map.

If you are not interested in Deathmatch mode, please try the "standard" versions (no gates) of this map:

http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/122140

This ziped file is actually a map-pack with 3 maps, better yet, a map with 3 Ã¯Â¿Â½flavoursÃ¯Â¿Â½:

de_favela_2010: This map is based on the last version de_favela_day, with practically the same lay-out and day lighting. This is the best version for gameplay.

de_favela_dusk: This map is a version with dusk/sun-set lighting.This version has a more interesting visual, however it makes difficult to see players in some parts because of the darkness, which harms a bit the gameplay. The use of night-vision is recommended in some parts. You can also improve visibility by adjusting the brightness level  by the counter-strike options menu.

de_favela_night: This map is a version with night lighting. The same comments go regarding players visibility as de_favela_dusk.

All 3 maps have the following improvements in relation to de_favela_day :

- The maps plays musics. The musics were not embedded into the bsp files, so the user can choose  his own musics to be played. The ziped file includes the folder de_favela with 6 musics. To install them, place this folder in the local folder ...counter-strike source/cstike/sound. If you wish to change the musics with your own, just save your mp3 files in this folder, and name them music1, music2, Ã¯Â¿Â½music6. All 6 musics can be played in each of the music players  in the map. To toggle musics, press <use key> (default Ã¯Â¿Â½EÃ¯Â¿Â½) facing the music player.

- The maps include special effects on C4 explosion.

- The maps have data-shows at CT and T spawns, which play slides. To toggle slides, press <use key> facing the keyboard.
